\frametitle {Simply-Typed Lambda Calculus} We begin with the simply-typed lambda calculus (no surprises so far): \par $$ \begin {array}{lrcl} \text {Type} & A & ::= & \Omega \mid A \rightarrow A \\ \text {Term} & M,\phi & ::= & x \mid \lambda x:A.M \mid M M \end {array} $$ \par \[ \infer {\Gamma \vdash \lambda x:A.M : A \rightarrow B}{\Gamma , x : A \vdash M : B} \qquad \infer {\Gamma \vdash M N : B} {\Gamma \vdash M : A \rightarrow B \quad \Gamma \vdash N : A} \] \beamer@mode \par 
